					<ul class="list-decimal list-inside">
						<li class="mt-3">Implementation is written in Zig.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Fuzz tested using libFuzzer.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Unit tests and integration tests are provided.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Heap allocations causing memory fragmentations are avoided.</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="mt-6">Networking</h2>
					<p>A custom event loop implementation is used for TCP/UDP networking across nodes.</p>

					<ul class="list-decimal list-inside">
						<li class="mt-3">Implementation is written in Zig.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Benchmarked to read/write 1.6GiB/sec.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Running a Rheia node requires one port to be open and available.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">The best available event dispatcher is used depending on the OS used to run a Rheia node.
							<p class="ml-4">a. io_uring/epoll for Linux.</p>
							<p class="ml-4">b. iommu for Windows.</p>
							<p class="ml-4">c. kqueue for Mac.</p>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2">
				<div>
					<h2>Cryptography</h2>
					<p>All cryptography in Rheia is handled by libsodium and Zig’s standard library.</p>

					<p class="mt-2">Networking</p>
					<ul class="list-decimal list-inside">
						<li class="mt-3">Session key establishment using Curve25519 Elliptic-Curve Diffie-Hellman (ECDH) Handshake.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Key derivation into outgoing/incoming symmetric keys using Blake2b 256-bit.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Session encryption/decryption using Chacha20-Poly1305.</li>
					</ul>

					<p class="mt-2">Identities</p>
					<ul class="list-decimal list-inside">
						<li class="mt-3">Ed25519 keypairs for node identities.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Ed25519 signatures for cryptographic attestations.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Kademlia overlay network for peer discovery/messaging.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				
				<div>
					<h2>Merk</h2>
					<p>A high-performance Merklized AVL Tree for storing account and state data in Rheia.</p>
					<ul class="list-decimal list-inside">
						<li class="mt-3">Implementation is written in Zig.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Data is represented as key-value pairs.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Zero-overhead reads, high-performance batch writes.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Large amounts of writes happen upon a block being finalized in Rheia.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Underlying key-value store is RocksDB.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Supports immutable checkpointing of the database at any point in time.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Supports being ran on a large variety of hardware, including memory-constrained devices.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2">
				<div>
					<h2>S/Kademlia</h2>
					<p>A p2p overlay networking protocol for securely bootstrapping, identifying, and anonymously routing messages across peers over an unreliable network.</p>
					<ul class="list-decimal list-inside">
						<li class="mt-3">Implementation is written in Zig.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Memory/disk usage for storing/handling routing tables per node is small and deterministic.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Peer IDs in S/Kademlia are periodically purged and recycled after long periods of inactivity.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Peer IDs are Ed25519 public keys which are constrained and generated using a static/dynamic cryptographic puzzle.</li>
						<li class="mt-3">Peer IDs are sorted on two axis.
							<p class="ml-4">a. The XOR distance of a peers identity against a nodes’ identity</p>
							<p class="ml-4">b. The responsiveness/ping frequency of a peer.</p>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div>
					<h2>WASM3</h2>
					<p>A high-performance WebAssembly interpreter used for running Rheia’s smart contracts.</p>
					<ul class="list-decimal list-inside">
